Farm Adventure Fun for Kids | Exploring Animals, Treats, and Surprises with Farmer Jason Welcome to Cog Hill Farm for Kids! In todays fun-filled farm adventure, Farmer Jason and Miss Holly take your little ones on an exciting exploration around the barn to meet all kinds of friendly farm animals! Join us as we introduce the kids to unique farm animals like donkeys, goats, chickens, a cow named Moody, and a sweet pig named Peaches. Your kids will love learning interesting facts about each animal, from how donkeys look like horses to what goats love to eat! Well even discover some amazing surprises for the animals like apples and pumpkins straight from the farm. Todays journey encourages curiosity and teaches young children to recognize different animals, the sounds they make, and even some fun words and letters perfect for toddlers, preschoolers, and kids ages 8 and under! Cog Hill Farm's Main Channel:    / @coghillfarm   Mrs. Cog Hill Farm's Channel:    / @mrscoghillfarm   Our Website: https://www.coghillfarm.com/ ------------- Welcome to Cog Hill Farm For Kids! This safe, fun-filled YouTube channel is perfect for younger children, designed to spark curiosity, laughter, and learning! Here at Cog Hill Farm, we introduce little ones to our wonderful world of animals in a gentle, educational way. From meeting our friendly animals like Holly the dog, Jess the mini donkey, Lovely Loretta the pig, and Nugget the emu, each episode offers exciting new adventures that teach kindness, compassion, and respect for animals. Our videos are filled with delightful animal antics, storytelling, and vibrant visuals that keep young viewers engaged while fostering a love for nature. Every episode is crafted to entertain while supporting early development in a nurturing, family-friendly environment. Parents can feel confident that Cog Hill Farm For Kids provides screen time that's wholesome, educational, and joy-filled! Join us in the magic of farm life and make Cog Hill Farm For Kids a fun and safe part of your familys journey! Thank you, Farmer Jason ...more
